Parliament, Monday, 11 May 2020 – The Portfolio Committee on Mineral Resources and Energy will tomorrow hold a virtual meeting to be briefed on the Annual Performance Plans (APP’s) and budgets of the Council for Geoscience (CGS), Mintek, and the Central Energy Fund (CEF) for the 2020/21 financial year.
	
	The CGS, Mintek and CEF are entities of the Department of Mineral Resources (DMRE), which already presented its own strategic and APP, as well as the 2020-2025 MTSF on 8 May 2020. In its presentation, the DMRE tabled an estimated budget of R9.3 billion for the current financial year.
	
	Furthermore, a joint meeting of the Standing Committee on Finance, together with the Select Committee on Finance has been postponed to Tuesday, 19 May 2020. The meeting was initially scheduled to take place tomorrow morning.
	
	Details of the meeting are as follows:
	Date:  Tuesday, 12 May 2020
	Time:  12:00-15:00
	
	The meetings will take place via Microsoft Teams/Zoom.
	Members of the media who would like to be part of the meetings to observe may forward their contact details to Mr Mlindi Mpindi on 081 716 7329 for inclusion in the Parliament Communications Service WhatsApp group, where login details will be shared.
	
	Members of the public may get involved and follow committee sittings live on Parliament TV (DStv Channel 408), via live stream on Parliament YouTube channel and Twitter page on the links below. You may subscribe to the Parliament YouTube channel to receive instant notification of live feeds.
	
